src/rqa.cpp (distance_matrix_cpp, rqa_line_stats_cpp) and R/rqa.R
(recurrence_matrix, rqa_measures)  (clean-room reimplementation from
published algorithms -- not a translation of any licensed or specified
source)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Algorithms:
  Eckmann JP, Kamphorst SO, Ruelle D. Recurrence plots of dynamical
  systems. Europhys Lett 1987;4(9):973-977.

  Zbilut JP, Webber CL Jr. Embeddings and delays as derived from
  quantification of recurrence plots. Phys Lett A 1992;171(3-4):199-203.

  Marwan N, Romano MC, Thiel M, Kurths J. Recurrence plots for the
  analysis of complex systems. Phys Rep 2007;438(5-6):237-329. (Used as
  the formula reference for RR/DET/L_mean/L_max/ENTR/LAM/TT, since these
  are defined consistently this way across major RQA toolboxes --
  Marwan's own CRP Toolbox, pyRQA, R's crqa/nonlinearTseries.)

No reference implementation was specified for this port (asked; no
preference given). Two design choices worth flagging explicitly since
they affect the numbers and aren't fixed by the algorithm alone:
  - Threshold convention: both fixed-radius and fixed-recurrence-rate
    (`rr`) thresholding are supported (`recurrence_matrix(radius = ...)`
    vs `recurrence_matrix(rr = ...)`); fixed-rr uses the empirical
    quantile of pairwise distances outside the Theiler band, which
    hits the target rate exactly by construction (no iterative search
    needed). Default when neither is given: `rr = 0.1`.
  - Theiler window: default `theiler_window = 1` excludes only the main
    diagonal (`i == j`) from all rate/line-length calculations; widen
    this for signals with strong short-range temporal autocorrelation
    that would otherwise inflate RR/DET with trivial "recurrences".
Not validated against an independent RQA implementation -- treat with
more caution than the other entries in this file until cross-checked
(e.g. against R's own `crqa` or `nonlinearTseries` packages, or
Marwan's CRP Toolbox, on a shared test signal).

